        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-large"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="684" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine-1024x684.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-91743" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine-768x513.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine-750x501.jpg 750w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/fire-engine.jpg 1204w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EFirefighters tackled a Smart car blaze in a Lake District town. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ECumbria police said they were called to Bowness-on-Windermere at around 5.30pm yesterday, Monday December 30. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ECumbria Fire and Rescue Service crews were already at the scene and the fire was extinguished at around 5.35pm. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe fire also caused damage to a nearby Toyota Yaris. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EBoth vehicles had been recovered by 8.30pm.  \u003C/p\u003E\n',
