    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="667" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-2.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-161915" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-2.jpg 1000w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-2-219x146.jpg 219w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-2-750x500.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe Met Office has issued weather warnings for high winds on New Year&#8217;s Eve in Cumbria.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe warning, from 7am until 11pm, said strong westerly winds were expected.  \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EIt said: &#8220;Strong and gusty south westerly winds will develop across southern Scotland and northeast England on Tuesday morning, veering to westerly during the evening. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E&#8220;Gusts of 50mph to 60mph are expected, perhaps reaching 70mph in a few exposed areas, and this may lead to some travel disruption.&#8221;\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Ch2 class="wp-block-heading"\u003EWhat should I expect?\u003C/h2\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cul class="wp-block-list"\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003ESome delays to road, rail, air and ferry transport are likely\u003C/li\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cli\u003EProbably some bus and train services affected, with some journeys taking longer\u003C/li\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cli\u003EDelays for high-sided vehicles on exposed routes and bridges likely\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="504" height="426" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weather-.png" alt="" class="wp-image-336009" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weather-.png 504w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weather--300x254.png 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weather--173x146.png 173w" sizes="(max-width: 504px) 100vw, 504px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EWeather warnings for snow and high winds on New Year&#8217;s Day have been removed. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe county was expected to see heavy and persistent snow as a band of rain with deep low pressure moved in from the west between 9am and 3am on Thursday. \u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
