    title: { rendered: 'Man dies while out in Lake District on Boxing Day' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="768" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LAMRT.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335952" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LAMRT.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LAMRT-300x225.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LAMRT-768x576.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LAMRT-195x146.jpg 195w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class="wp-element-caption"\u003EPicture: Langdale Ambleside Mountain Rescue Team \u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ELake District mountain rescue teams were called out on Boxing Day after a man was reported to be unconscious.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ELangdale Ambleside Mountain Rescue Team volunteers were called at around 2.55pm to Grisedale Hause and 13 members responded \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe team said: &#8220;CPR was unsuccessful  and he was sadly declared deceased. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E&#8220;He was recovered to Keswick Mountain Rescue Team base by a Coastguard helicopter.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E&#8220;We were assisted by Coniston and Keswick mountain rescue teams.&#8221; \u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
