    title: { rendered: 'Windows damaged at Whitehaven pub' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="668" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/police-generic-4.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-114714" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/police-generic-4.jpg 1000w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/police-generic-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/police-generic-4-768x513.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/police-generic-4-750x501.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPolice are appealing for information after two windows were damaged at a Whitehaven pub.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe incident happened at the Royal Standard on West Strand at around 7.30pm on Thursday December 19.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe suspect is described as being a white male, between the ages of 40 and 50, with short dark hair and around 6ft.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EHe was wearing a black crew sweatshirt, blue denim jeans and white trainers.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPolice believe he left the pub with four other men of a similar age.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EOfficers said they have made CCTV enquiries and request that the person responsible make contact with the police.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAnyone with information relating to this incident can report online at \u003Ca href="https://www.cumbria.police.uk/reportit"\u003Ewww.cumbria.police.uk/report-it\u003C/a\u003E, quoting incident number 164 of 21 December or call 101.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAlternatively contact Crimestoppers, anonymously, on 0800 555 111.\u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '\u003Cp\u003EPolice are appealing for information after two windows were damaged at a Whitehaven pub.\u003C/p\u003E\n', protected: false },
