        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="752" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/copeland-police-.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335872" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/copeland-police-.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/copeland-police--300x220.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/copeland-police--768x564.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/copeland-police--199x146.jpg 199w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class="wp-element-caption"\u003EPicture: Copeland Police \u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe A595 has reopened after an incident earlier this evening. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe road was closed between Gosforth and Holmrook as police dealt with the incident just after 5pm. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ECopeland police said: &#8220;Thank you to the locals for assisting with this incident; you were a great help and we couldn&#8217;t have done it without you.&#8221; \u003C/p\u003E\n',
