        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="430" height="287" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Alan-Hiwa.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335764" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Alan-Hiwa.jpg 430w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Alan-Hiwa-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Alan-Hiwa-219x146.jpg 219w" sizes="(max-width: 430px) 100vw, 430px" /\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class="wp-element-caption"\u003EAlan Hiwa\u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPolice are concerned for the welfare of a missing 16-year-old from Penrith.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAlan Hiwa was last seen in the area of the town&#8217;s Huntley Avenue at around 3.30pm on December 24.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAlan is described as 5ft 9ins, and slim with black hair.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca\u003E\u003C/a\u003EAnyone with information should contact police on 101.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EOfficers would also like to urge Alan to contact this number if he sees this appeal.\u003C/p\u003E\n',
