    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/25/ex-workington-comet-sam-mcgurk-signs-for-birmingham-bulls/',
    title: { rendered: 'Ex-Workington Comet Sam McGurk signs for Birmingham Bulls' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-large"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-1024x683.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-223771" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-219x146.jpg 219w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-1320x880.jpg 1320w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-750x500.jpg 750w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Sam-McGurk-3.jpg 1800w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class="wp-element-caption"\u003ESam McGurk. Picture: Dave Payne\u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EBirmingham have completed their National Development Trophy side for the 2025 season.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EMax James and Sam McGurk are the final two signings for the Bulls, with Max Broadhurst named as their No.8.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EManager Laurence Rogers said: “Max James took some big steps in the right direction with Leicester in the National Development League this year and he’ll be a key rider for us.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E“Sam is only 18 and for me he is a highly promising youngster. He gained a lot more experience with Workington this year and he’ll really kick on from that next season I think.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E“I’m glad we’ve been able to bring in Max Broadhurst as the Bulls’ No8 &#8211; he was a Buffalo in 2024, he’s secured an NDL spot with Oxford and it’s going to be good to have him as part of the squad.”\u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '\u003Cp\u003EBirmingham have completed their National Development Trophy side for the 2025 season.\u003C/p\u003E\n', protected: false },
