    title: { rendered: 'Woman banned from Carlisle stores for five years' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-large"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="670" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Claire-Sproat--1024x670.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335489" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Claire-Sproat--1024x670.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Claire-Sproat--300x196.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Claire-Sproat--768x503.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Claire-Sproat--223x146.jpg 223w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Claire-Sproat-.jpg 1204w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class="wp-element-caption"\u003EClaire Sproat\u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EA Carlisle woman has been banned from city stores for five years. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ECarlisle Neighbourhood Policing Team secured the Criminal Behaviour Order at North and West Magistrates’ Court or Claire Sproat, 44, of Howard Place. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EShe is banned from entering any premises part of the Carlisle Shopwatch or Retailers Against Crime scheme and is also banned from having an unsealed vessel containing alcohol in any public place, except inside a licensed premises.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe order follows Sproat breaching a Community Protection Notice and for a shoplifting offence.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EShe was given an £80 fine for the breach.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPC Andrew Beal, from Carlisle and Wigton Neighbourhood Policing Team, said: “This order will prevent Sproat from further criminality and help protect business owners and local residents.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E“I would encourage anyone who witnesses the terms of such a court order being broken to contact the police immediately.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E&#8220;The punishment for breaking the terms of an order can be up to five years in prison.”\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAnyone who witnesses  Sproat breaching the terms of her order should contact the police.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
