    modified_gmt: '2024-12-24T11:58:57',
    slug: 'service-to-celebrate-life-of-man-killed-in-kirkby-lonsdale-fire',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/23/service-to-celebrate-life-of-man-killed-in-kirkby-lonsdale-fire/',
    title: { rendered: 'Service to celebrate life of man killed in Kirkby Lonsdale fire' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="768" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Kirkby-Lonsdale-fire-7.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334134" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Kirkby-Lonsdale-fire-7.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Kirkby-Lonsdale-fire-7-300x225.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Kirkby-Lonsdale-fire-7-768x576.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Kirkby-Lonsdale-fire-7-195x146.jpg 195w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EA service to celebrate the life of the man killed in a fire at Kirkby Lonsdale earlier this month will be held.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe memorial for Ben Taylor, 45, who lived on Market Street, will be held on Monday December 30 at 12.30pm at Beetham Hall Crematorium, near Milnthorpe.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe full service will also be live streamed to St Mary’s Church, Kirkby Lonsdale from 12.30pm.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EOnly family flowers are requested but an invitation for donations to go into a fund to commemorate Mr Taylor’s memory can be left at the funeral service or sent to Edward Waller, JJ Martin Funeral Directors, 4 Harling Bank, Kirkby Lonsdale, Carnforth, Lancs, LA6 2DJ or call 01524 272431.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EMr Taylor&#8217;s family have thanked the Kirkby Lonsdale community for all their support and kindness.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EEmergency services were called to the town at 5.45am on Sunday December 8  to a blaze at apartments opposite the Red Dragon pub on Main Street.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E75 firefighters and 10 crews were called to the incident, plus the aerial ladders from Carlisle and Barrow.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href="https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/21/kirkby-lonsdale-fire-cordons-lift-on-main-street-as-79000-raised-for-disaster-fund/"\u003EThe Kirkby Lonsdale Disaster Relief Fund has been set up and has so far raised over £81,000 for the community still affected by the fire&#8217;s aftermath. \u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href="https://bit.ly/3ZOXO2q"\u003EAn inquest has opened into Mr Taylor&#8217;s death.\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered: '\u003Cp\u003EA service to celebrate the life of the man killed in a fire at Kirkby Lonsdale earlier this month will be held.\u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
