    slug: 'arrests-after-police-drugs-raids-in-west-cumbria',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/23/arrests-after-police-drugs-raids-in-west-cumbria/',
    title: { rendered: 'Arrests after police drugs raids in West Cumbria' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-305494" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7-220x146.jpg 220w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPolice have arrested two people after carrying out drugs raids in West Cumbria.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EOfficers raided three properties in Mirehouse in Whitehaven on Thursday at Meadow Road, Latrigg Road and Derwentwater Road.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThey were conducted by officers from intel, neighbourhood policing, tactical support, roads policing, dog unit, CID and community serious organised crime.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAt a property on Meadow Road officers arrested a 29-year-old man from Whitehaven on suspicion of being concerned in the supply of class A drugs.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EHe was released under investigation.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EA 43-year-old man from Wigan was also arrested on A590 between Newby Bridge and Levens on suspicion of being concerned in the supply of class A drugs and his vehicle seized. He was released under investigation.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EA &nbsp;spokesman from the force&#8217;s intelligence unit said: “These warrants were only made possible by information provided from the community.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E“We rely on the community to be our eyes and ears, so we can challenge the use and supply of drugs.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E“We have contempt for the act of criminality, which has no place in our communities.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003E“If you suspect criminality is taking place in your neighbourhood then we want to hear from you so we can take action.”\u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '\u003Cp\u003EPolice have arrested two people after carrying out drugs raids in West Cumbria.\u003C/p\u003E\n', protected: false },
