    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/22/police-search-after-child-reported-as-on-their-own-in-egremont/',
    title: { rendered: 'UPDATE: Police search after child reported as on their own in Egremont' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="752" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/police-5.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-162008" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/police-5.jpg 1000w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/police-5-300x226.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/police-5-768x578.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/police-5-194x146.jpg 194w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/police-5-750x564.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPolice mounted a search in the Egremont area after a report that a child was spotted on their own.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe report was made at around 8pm yesterday, Sunday December 22, when it was reported that a boy was seen on the town&#8217;s Main Street at around 7.10pm.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003ECumbria police said officers had carried out extensive enquiries in the surrounding area but had not found a child.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAlthough the boy was first reported to be around five years old and wearing pyjamas, police said CCTV enquiries had established the boy looked to be around 10.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAt 8.40am today, Monday December 23, police issued an update saying the boy had been identified and no concerns reported. \u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
