    title: { rendered: 'Flood alert issued for Lake District river' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\u003Cdiv class="wp-block-image"\u003E\n\u003Cfigure class="aligncenter size-full"\u003E\u003Cimg loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="667" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-6.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-161919" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-6.jpg 1000w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-6-219x146.jpg 219w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/umbrella-6-750x500.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EA flood alert has been issued for a Lake District river. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe alert means flooding is possible and people should be prepared. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe alert is for the Upper River Derwent, Stonethwaite Beck and Derwentwater.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EFollowing recent heavy rain, the Lodore gauge has reached flood alert.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EFlooding is possible at locations near the Upper River Derwent, Stonethwaite Beck and Derwentwater, with low lying land and roads expected to be most affected, particularly around the Upper Derwent from Seathwaite to Derwentwater.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe forecast is to improve with some showers over the weekend.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EPeople are urged to avoid walking, cycling or driving through flood water. Avoid using low lying footpaths and any bridges near local watercourses.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\n\n\u003Cp\u003EIt is not expected that a flood warning will be issued for this area, and river and rainfall levels will continue to be monitored. \u003C/p\u003E\n',
      protected: false,
    },
