    modified_gmt: '2024-12-21T05:22:39',
    slug: 'ufos-or-drones-strange-lights-spotted-in-cumbrias-skies',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/20/ufos-or-drones-strange-lights-spotted-in-cumbrias-skies/',
    title: { rendered: 'UFOs or drones? Strange lights spotted in Cumbria&#8217;s skies' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="650" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-one.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335114" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-one.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-one-300x190.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-one-768x488.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-one-230x146.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Cumbria Crack</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Strange lights have been spotted in skies across Cumbria. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Large bright circular objects have been spotted low down in the sky in Kendal, Windermere and Egremont. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It comes after unidentified objects were also photographed and recorded flying towards an RAF base in Cornwall earlier this week. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is not known if the objects are connected to a number of unidentified drones that were spotted over military RAF bases in the South of England over the past few weeks, as reported by the BBC.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A walker &#8211; who does not wish to be named &#8211; photographed one of the objects in Egremont. </p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="534" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-three.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335115" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-three.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-three-300x156.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-three-768x401.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-three-260x136.jpg 260w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Cumbria Crack</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The individual said the object made no noise and appeared to be much larger and brighter than anything they had ever seen in the night sky before.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They added it was spotted much lower than where planets or satellites are typically seen.</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="600" height="800" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-two-rotated.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335116" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-two-rotated.jpg 600w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-two-225x300.jpg 225w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drone-two-110x146.jpg 110w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">A close up image of the object. Picture: Cumbria Crack</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Others have also taken to social media to share similar images of the unidentified objects that they claimed were as big as a car. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>These lights were spotted over Vulcan Park in Workington at around 5am on December 1 by Jenna Holliday: </p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="600" height="800" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jenna-Holliday-.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335139" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jenna-Holliday-.jpg 600w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jenna-Holliday--225x300.jpg 225w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jenna-Holliday--110x146.jpg 110w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Over Vulcan Park, Workington. Picture: Jenna Holliday </figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Have you seen any similar objects in Cumbria&#8217;s skies? Send us your stories and pictures at <a href="mailto:admin@cumbriacrack.com">admin@cumbriacrack.com</a></p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
