        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="807" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Anthony-Murray-Ben-Challis.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-117582" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Anthony-Murray-Ben-Challis.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Anthony-Murray-Ben-Challis-300x236.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Anthony-Murray-Ben-Challis-768x605.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Anthony-Murray-Ben-Challis-750x591.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Anthony Murray (Ben Challis)</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Five triallists have signed for Whitehaven.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Harley Nelson and Aaron Burns, of Kells, Emerson Allen and Mitchell Todd, of Lowca, and Ben Atkinson, of Dalton have been announced as joining the side.\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The five players have been part of the pre-season training and have signed trialist forms which will allow them the opportunity to play in the pre-season clashes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Head coach Anthony Murray said: \u201cWe will be giving them an opportunity. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;They need to play and show what they can do, they\u2019ve showed what they can do in training and I\u2019ve been really impressed, worked hard and come in with a good attitude and a really good skill set.</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?height=476&#038;href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FWhitehavenRLFC2010%2Fvideos%2F2057497374767135%2F&#038;show_text=false&#038;width=267&#038;t=0" width="267" height="476" style="border:none;overflow:hidden" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true" allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowFullScreen="true"></iframe>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Fair play to the community clubs around here that have been coaching these lads, I\u2019m really pleased with that and impressed with what is going on locally.\u201d</p>\n',
