    modified_gmt: '2024-12-20T11:10:32',
    slug: 'cumbrian-accounting-firm-rewards-top-whitehaven-business-student',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/20/cumbrian-accounting-firm-rewards-top-whitehaven-business-student/',
    title: { rendered: 'Cumbrian accounting firm rewards top Whitehaven business student' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="627" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Stuart-Edgar-Anezka-Feckova-and-Paul-Charlton.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-335087" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Stuart-Edgar-Anezka-Feckova-and-Paul-Charlton.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Stuart-Edgar-Anezka-Feckova-and-Paul-Charlton-300x184.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Stuart-Edgar-Anezka-Feckova-and-Paul-Charlton-768x470.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Stuart-Edgar-Anezka-Feckova-and-Paul-Charlton-238x146.jpg 238w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Stuart Edgar, Anezka Feckova and Paul Charlton</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A Whitehaven student has been honoured for her outstanding academic achievements by a leading Cumbrian accountancy firm. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anezka Feckova, of St Benedict&#8217;s Catholic High School, was given Lamont Pridmore&#8217;s Business Student of the Year 2024 award.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The award celebrates students who demonstrate exceptional dedication, talent, and understanding of the business world.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anezka\u2019s hard work and commitment throughout her A-level business studies earned her this prestigious recognition and placed her among the top students at St Benedict\u2019s.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Paul Charlton, head of computer science and business at the school, nominated Anezka. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>He said: \u201cAnezka was selected for this award due to her unwavering commitment and dedication to her business course.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;She is extremely hardworking and achieved some incredible examination scores. Anezka produced two high-quality portfolios for her other units of work, resulting in an overall final grade of a Distinction * (A*).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;These portfolios were well-written, well-presented, and demonstrated a clear, well-developed understanding of the business world. Anezka was well-liked by her peers and by the staff who had the pleasure of teaching her.\u201d</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stuart Edgar, managing director of Lamont Pridmore West Cumbria, presented the award to Anezka during the ceremony.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>He said: \u201cAnezka is a remarkable student. It is clear that her hard work and passion for learning will lead to great success in the future.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;We are delighted to support students like Anezka who are setting the standard for academic excellence in our community.\u201d</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anezka is now continuing her education at York University, where she is pursuing a degree in law.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lamont Pridmore remains dedicated to recognising and supporting academic excellence in business education.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>A Whitehaven student has been honoured for her outstanding academic achievements by a leading Cumbrian accountancy firm. </p>\n', protected: false },
