    modified: '2024-12-20T09:32:20',
    modified_gmt: '2024-12-20T09:32:20',
    slug: 'drugs-raid-in-barrow-leads-to-three-men-in-court',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/20/drugs-raid-in-barrow-leads-to-three-men-in-court/',
    title: { rendered: 'Drugs raid in Barrow leads to three men in court' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="690" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Workington-magistrates-court-4-1024x690-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-248446" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Workington-magistrates-court-4-1024x690-1.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Workington-magistrates-court-4-1024x690-1-300x202.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Workington-magistrates-court-4-1024x690-1-768x518.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Workington-magistrates-court-4-1024x690-1-217x146.jpg 217w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Workington-magistrates-court-4-1024x690-1-750x505.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A drugs raid in Barrow has resulted in three men appearing in court for a total of 18 charges. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Police carried out the raid on Wednesday and found class A drugs worth around \u00a35,000, cash and drugs paraphernalia.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The raid was executed as part of an investigation into suspected county lines drug dealing in Barrow.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Carl Wilkinson, 44, of Broad Street, Barrow, and Ethan Barber, 21 and Jordan Brownfield, 19, both of Stoke, were charged with:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class="wp-block-list">\n<li>Possession with intent to supply heroin and crack cocaine</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Being concerned in the supply of heroin and crack cocaine</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Possession of criminal property</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Possession of an offensive weapon</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Detectives secured 18 charges in total against the three men.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All appeared before Barrow Magistrates Court yesterday, Thursday December 19. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wilkinson was remanded into custody. Barber and Brownfield have been bailed until a further hearing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cumbria police said: \u201cCumbria police take drug supply within our communities extremely seriously and continue to\u00a0target those who come into our communities to supply class A drugs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cDrugs and the criminality associated with their supply, can have devastating impacts on local communities.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cWe would urge members of the public to come forward with any information so that we can continue to make our communities safer.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyone with information can report online at\u00a0<a href="http://www.cumbria.police.uk/report-it">www.cumbria.police.uk/report-it</a> or contact Crimestoppers anonymously via 0800 555 111.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>A drugs raid in Barrow has resulted in three men appearing in court for a total of 18 charges. </p>\n', protected: false },
