    title: { rendered: 'Early hours rescue of person from Maryport harbour' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="850" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Coastguard-.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-325073" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Coastguard-.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Coastguard--300x249.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Coastguard--768x638.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Coastguard--176x146.jpg 176w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Whitehaven Coastguard Rescue Team </figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Emergency services were called out in the early hours of yesterday to help a person at Maryport harbour.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Maryport Coastguard Rescue Team, Whitehaven Coastguard Rescue Team, Cumbria police and the North West Ambulance Service were called yesterday, Thursday December 19, after concerns of a person&#8217;s welfare in the Shipping Brow area.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The person inadvertently entered the water after they slipped.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whitehaven Coastguard Rescue Team said: &#8220;A Coastguard Rescue Swimmer was deployed to secure the casualty while recovery was made into Maryport Rescue&#8217;s emergency rescue boat, before being transferred to the lifeboat slip and into the care of the ambulance crew.&#8221;</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
