    title: { rendered: 'Mountain biker dies in Lake District forest' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="720" height="540" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/KMRT.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334986" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/KMRT.jpg 720w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/KMRT-300x225.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/KMRT-195x146.jpg 195w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Keswick Mountain Rescue Team </figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A mountain biker has died after he was found in a Lake District forest. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keswick Mountain Rescue Team said they were called to Whinlatter Forest on Monday, December 16 at around 6.20pm.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>A mountain biker on the red north trail came across an unresponsive lone male biker. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The passer-by immediately commenced CPR and called the emergency services. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Keswick team said they arrived and continued attempts at resuscitation. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The team added: &#8220;Sadly and despite best efforts, nothing could be done to save the man. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Our thoughts and sympathies are with the man\u2019s family and friends.&#8221;</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>A mountain biker has died after he was found in a Lake District forest. </p>\n', protected: false },
