    title: { rendered: 'Police vehicle&#8217;s tyre damaged by vandals' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="500" height="315" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/police-car-window-anpr-1.jpg" alt="A police car window viewed from the side with a Cumbria Constabulary logo accompanied by the words Safer Stronger Cumbria" class="wp-image-46076" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/police-car-window-anpr-1.jpg 500w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/police-car-window-anpr-1-300x189.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A police vehicle&#8217;s tyre was damaged in Carlisle.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The marked vehicle was parked at Borrowdale Gardens between 10am and noon on Monday December 9. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The police officer was dealing with an incident in the area and was them dispatched to another incident. The officer noticed the damage as he was responding to the incident.\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cumbria police said: &#8220;The vandalism not only put the officer at significant risk it delayed the response to the victim of the incident they were trying to respond to.&#8221; <br><br>Anyone who witnessed the damage or has CCTV or dash camera footage is asked to call Cumbria police on 101 and quote log 100 of 9 December 2024.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, call Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
