    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/19/reduced-rugby-union-programme/',
    title: { rendered: 'Reduced rugby union programme' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="687" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Liam-McAvoy-is-part-of-a-two-man-tackle-that-knocked-the-Stoke-2nd-row-back-onto-the-ground.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-328970" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Liam-McAvoy-is-part-of-a-two-man-tackle-that-knocked-the-Stoke-2nd-row-back-onto-the-ground.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Liam-McAvoy-is-part-of-a-two-man-tackle-that-knocked-the-Stoke-2nd-row-back-onto-the-ground-300x201.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Liam-McAvoy-is-part-of-a-two-man-tackle-that-knocked-the-Stoke-2nd-row-back-onto-the-ground-768x515.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Liam-McAvoy-is-part-of-a-two-man-tackle-that-knocked-the-Stoke-2nd-row-back-onto-the-ground-218x146.jpg 218w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: David Nattrass</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>There\u2019s a reduced programme on Saturday as Cumbria rugby union winds down for the seasonal break.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Counties 1 Cumbria have already started their Christmas/New Year break and will resume on January 4.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Penrith have an attractive game to finish on in 2024 as fourth in the table Manchester visit Winters Park.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cumbrians gave one of their worst performances of the season last week at Leek and will surely want to make amends against a good Manchester side.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In contrast Kendal put up a superb display against leaders Rossendale before losing 35-20 and something similar against a fading Blackburn side could provide a pre-Christmas tonic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Regional 2 North top game is a county derby between Keswick and an improving Kirby Lonsdale.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both had good wins last week and Keswick are showing signs of breaking into the top half of the table. Martin Maughan has this one to control.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sadly Carlisle have gone into reverse gear after a promising start to the season, and was encapsuled in their 20-0 defeat at bottom side Kirkby Lonsdale last week.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They have an attractive home game against second in the table Middlesbrough and the visitors are bringing two teams over.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A late fitness test will decide which referee takes this one. Jonny Watson will take the second team game.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The other two Cumbrian sides both end 2024 on the road \u2013 Aspatria go to Morpeth and Upper Eden are at Consett.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
