    slug: 'university-of-cumbria-leader-presented-with-obe',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/19/university-of-cumbria-leader-presented-with-obe/',
    title: { rendered: 'University of Cumbria leader presented with OBE' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="670" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Prof-Webster-Henderson--1024x670.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334832" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Prof-Webster-Henderson--1024x670.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Prof-Webster-Henderson--300x196.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Prof-Webster-Henderson--768x503.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Prof-Webster-Henderson--223x146.jpg 223w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Prof-Webster-Henderson-.jpg 1204w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Professor Brian Webster-Henderson</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A University of Cumbria leader has been presented with his OBE by the King. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Deputy Vice Chancellor Professor Brian Webster-Henderson was named in the King\u2019s Birthday Honours list for his services to the NHS and education.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Prof Webster-Henderson travelled to London this week for the investiture at Buckingham Palace, where he was presented with his OBE by King Charles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A professor of nursing, Prof Webster-Henderson is a recognised and established national leader in relation to nursing education, healthcare and workforce development who was awarded a prestigious Fellowship of the Queen\u2019s Nursing Institute in 2022.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>His career in nursing, higher education and academia stretches more than four decades and continues to see him working at the highest, national levels of strategic discussions and workforce development, curriculum, research and policy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Building upon this wealth of experience, Prof Webster-Henderson is currently spearheading the establishment of the\u00a0Pears Cumbria School of Medicine, a unique partnership between Imperial College London and University of Cumbria, which welcomes its first students in August 2025.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>He is also part of the University of Cumbria team working with Cumberland Council on the\u00a0Cumberland Health Determinants Research Collaboration\u00a0(HDRC).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cumberland HDRC is a \u00a34.8m project funded by the National Institute for Health and Care Research to create a research informed approach to excellent services within the Cumberland council area.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In his role as Deputy Vice Chancellor, Prof Webster-Henderson provides executive leadership across University of Cumbria\u2019s academic, research and knowledge exchange operations and its student support services.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>He also leads on the university\u2019s equality, diversity, inclusion, and well-being agendas, and is a strategic advisor on education, research and workforce to the executive board of University Hospitals of Morecambe Bay NHS Foundation Trust and a trustee for the Cumbria Education Trust.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A proud Scot hailing from Carnoustie, Prof Webster-Henderson said: \u201cIt was such a surprise to be included in the King\u2019s Birthday Honours List in June and it is a delight now to be able to attend an official investiture.\u201d</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
