    title: { rendered: 'Burglar &#8216;rummages through Christmas presents&#8217; at West Cumbrian home' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-305494" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/police-generic-7-220x146.jpg 220w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Police are investigating a reported burglary at a West Cumbrian home. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Someone entered a property at St George\u2019s Terrace, Bransty, Whitehaven at around 6.35am yesterday, Wednesday December 18, and rummaged through Christmas presents. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>They were wearing dark clothes and jumped a gate at the back of the property when leaving.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Police are appealing for witnesses, anyone with information or anyone with relevant CCTV to come forward.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyone with information can report online at\u00a0<a href="http://www.cumbria.police.uk/report-it" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">www.cumbria.police.uk/report-it</a> quoting incident 32 of December 18 or call 101.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, contact Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
