    title: { rendered: 'Four pregnant sheep killed and three injured by dog' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="666" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sheep.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-164488" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sheep.jpg 1000w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sheep-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sheep-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sheep-219x146.jpg 219w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sheep-750x500.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Four sheep were killed and three were injured by a dog in north Cumbria. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Police are investigating the incident of sheep worrying, which happened in a field off the A6071 towards Longtown, on Monday, December 9 at around 11am. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is believed all sheep were pregnant ewes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The dog, described as a German shepherd, was seen attacking sheep. It was by itself. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>During the incident, the dog was destroyed by the livestock owner, as is their right under the legislation in the protection of livestock.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you believe this may be your dog, which has been missing since December 9, contact PC 2232 Mann or PC 3552 Hannan on 101.<br><br>Anyone with information is asked to contact Cumbria police on 101 and quote log 109 of 9 December 2024.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Or Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
