    title: { rendered: 'Win for Kirkby Lonsdale gives side hope' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="677" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Kirkby-Lonsdale-.png" alt="" class="wp-image-230496" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Kirkby-Lonsdale-.png 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Kirkby-Lonsdale--300x198.png 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Kirkby-Lonsdale--768x508.png 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Kirkby-Lonsdale--221x146.png 221w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Kirkby-Lonsdale--750x496.png 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Robin Ree </figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Kirkby Lonsdale had a rare win in Regional Two North to give them hope that they can avoid another relegation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They were 20-0 home winners against Carlisle which was another disappointing result for the visitors who have hit a poor run of results after a bright start to the season.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kirkby Lonsdale scored three tries, so the four-try bonus point still eluded them. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However the encouraging performance in a 31-15 defeat against Durham City last week continued.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Everyone put in a big shift in defence to keep a clean sheet, and again there were lots of spirit and endeavour to move the ball around.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Right winger Tom Barnes scored two tries, and left winger Charlie Oates went full length after an interception.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Their visit to Keswick on Saturday will be interesting, as they will be seeking revenge after their defeat earlier in the season at Kirkby Lonsdale.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A minute\u2019s silence was held before the game, a tribute to Ben Taylor who lost his life in the fire last weekend, and also for long standing club member, official and supporter Mike Martindale, who died during the week.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>Kirkby Lonsdale had a rare win in Regional Two North to give them hope that they can avoid another relegation.</p>\n', protected: false },
