    slug: 'free-car-park-opens-in-appleby-this-week',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/18/free-car-park-opens-in-appleby-this-week/',
    title: { rendered: 'Free car park opens in Appleby this week' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Edenside-Car-Park.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334715" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Edenside-Car-Park.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Edenside-Car-Park-300x171.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Edenside-Car-Park-768x438.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Edenside-Car-Park-256x146.jpg 256w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A temporary free car park will open in Appleby this week. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The car park, on the site of the former Edenside Care Home, will be opened by the Environment Agency on Friday, December 20. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It has been created to ease potential disruption for residents and visitors while construction work associated with the town\u2019s new flood defence scheme at the existing Broad Close car park continues.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The construction site closes for the Christmas holiday on Friday.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>From mid-February, service diversions will start in Chapel Street which will require traffic management.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An Environment Agency spokesman said: \u201cWe are committed to reducing the potential impact of our flood risk management scheme construction on the Appleby community.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;The temporary car&nbsp;park demonstrates our commitment&nbsp;to supporting residents and visitors during this crucial project to better protect 64 properties in the town from flooding and provide \u00a321 million in economic benefits to Appleby.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cWe appreciate the community&#8217;s patience and cooperation as we work towards enhancing Appleby&#8217;s flood resilience.\u201d</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>A temporary free car park will open in Appleby this week.</p>\n', protected: false },
