    title: { rendered: 'Deer Orchard&#8217;s abandoned game will count' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="704" height="362" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/fundraiser-deer-orchard.png" alt="" class="wp-image-301333" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/fundraiser-deer-orchard.png 704w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/fundraiser-deer-orchard-300x154.png 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/fundraiser-deer-orchard-260x134.png 260w" sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Deer Orchard </figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Deer Orchard\u2019s abandoned game with Dearham Commercial will count after the West Cumberland Sunday League committee ruled the result stands.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Dearham started with eight, were soon down to seven through injury and a second player indicated he was not able to continue at half-time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Down to six players the referee had no option but to abandon the game, although Dearham had been prepared to forfeit the points.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They had suffered four cry-offs on the morning of the match and that effectively rule out their title challenge after a good start to the season.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Orchard, however, are still in with a shout for the Premier Division championship, currently six points behind leaders Northside with three games in hand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reigning champions Northside have three games to play while Orchard have six more fixtures to fit in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Grabbing the goals on Sunday were Keith Skillen (3), Mike Graham (2), Luke Graham, Louis Pickering, Sam Wright and Ben Rathbone.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered: '<p>Deer Orchard\u2019s abandoned game with Dearham Commercial will count after the West Cumberland Sunday League committee ruled the result stands.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
