    title: { rendered: 'Vinnie Foord set to soar at Kent Eagles' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Workington-Comets-have-signed-an-exciting-all-action-British-youngster-Vinnie-Foord-for-the-2025-season.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-328757" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Workington-Comets-have-signed-an-exciting-all-action-British-youngster-Vinnie-Foord-for-the-2025-season.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Workington-Comets-have-signed-an-exciting-all-action-British-youngster-Vinnie-Foord-for-the-2025-season-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Workington-Comets-have-signed-an-exciting-all-action-British-youngster-Vinnie-Foord-for-the-2025-season-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Workington-Comets-have-signed-an-exciting-all-action-British-youngster-Vinnie-Foord-for-the-2025-season-219x146.jpg 219w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Vinnie Foord. Picture: Dave Payne</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Workington Comets\u2019 reserve recruit Vinnie Foord will be lining up in the new National Development Trophy for Kent Eagles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 18-year-old Foord, who will form a new reserve partnership for the Comets, is set to be third heat-leader for the Eagles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Foord, based in East Sussex, made his NDL debut with Kent in 2021 before spending the next three years with Leicester, and also stepped up to the Championship this year where he enjoyed success and progression with Poole.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Eagles co-owner David Graveling said: \u201cWe are very pleased to have secured his services for our first season in league racing at Iwade.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cVinnie has got to where he is the hard way. He is a never say die performer who never gives up.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cWe look forward to working closely with him. He is most definitely a potential star of the future, and we would take immense pride in being a part of his journey.\u201d</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
