    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/18/lake-district-farm-set-to-go-under-hammer-for-900000/',
    title: { rendered: 'Lake District farm set to go under hammer for \u00a3900,000' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="768" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Simpson-Ground-Farm.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334649" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Simpson-Ground-Farm.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Simpson-Ground-Farm-300x225.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Simpson-Ground-Farm-768x576.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Simpson-Ground-Farm-195x146.jpg 195w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Simpson Ground Farm</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A Lake District farm is set to go under the hammer at an auction in February. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simpson Ground Farm, between the Cartmel and Winster Valleys, will be auctioned by H&amp;H Lakes &amp; Estates at Kendal Town Hall on February 6.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The four-bedroom farmhouse and an extensive range of traditional farm buildings, plus over 4.23 acres of land, are available as a single lot with a guide price of \u00a3900,000 to \u00a3950,000. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The second lot is for a detached converted two-bedroom barn with 4.9 acres, with a guide price of \u00a360,000 to \u00a370,000. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>H&amp;H Land &amp; Estates director, Mark Barrow, said: \u201cSimpson Ground Farm is everything that rural property buyers dream about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;This is a golden chance to acquire a traditional farmhouse and buildings surrounded by your own land in a stunning location in the Lake District National Park with breathtaking 360\u00b0 views.&#8221;</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>A Lake District farm is set to go under the hammer at an auction in February. </p>\n', protected: false },
