    modified_gmt: '2024-12-18T09:56:37',
    slug: 'keswick-head-coach-praises-commitment-of-team',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/18/keswick-head-coach-praises-commitment-of-team/',
    title: { rendered: 'Keswick head coach praises commitment of team' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="667" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Dan-Craghill-dives-in-for-Keswick-2nds-third-try-Ben-Challis.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334035" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Dan-Craghill-dives-in-for-Keswick-2nds-third-try-Ben-Challis.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Dan-Craghill-dives-in-for-Keswick-2nds-third-try-Ben-Challis-300x195.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Dan-Craghill-dives-in-for-Keswick-2nds-third-try-Ben-Challis-768x500.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Dan-Craghill-dives-in-for-Keswick-2nds-third-try-Ben-Challis-224x146.jpg 224w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dan Craghill dives in for Keswick 2nds&#8217; third try (Ben Challis)</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Keswick head coach Garry Holmes has been praising the progress of the club\u2019s second team.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Following victories for both senior teams at the weekend Holmes said: &#8220;Our Cumbria 1 team continues to build and support the men&#8217;s squad by being more competitive.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cWe had changes in the 2nd XV throughout the week, right up until Saturday morning, which is a testament to how hard our boys are working on and off the pitch, for the team and for the open age men&#8217;s squad as a whole.</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="891" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Leo-Horsbrugh-cramped-up-as-he-dived-in-to-score-Keswicks-final-try-Ben-Challis.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334034" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Leo-Horsbrugh-cramped-up-as-he-dived-in-to-score-Keswicks-final-try-Ben-Challis.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Leo-Horsbrugh-cramped-up-as-he-dived-in-to-score-Keswicks-final-try-Ben-Challis-300x261.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Leo-Horsbrugh-cramped-up-as-he-dived-in-to-score-Keswicks-final-try-Ben-Challis-768x668.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Leo-Horsbrugh-cramped-up-as-he-dived-in-to-score-Keswicks-final-try-Ben-Challis-168x146.jpg 168w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Leo Horsbrugh cramped up as he dived in to score Keswick&#8217;s final try (Ben Challis)</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>\u201cOur Seconds season is now on the Christmas break until the new year, but we need to back up the win at Aspatria next weekend with another big performance against a proud Kirkby Lonsdale team.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cDespite being bottom of the Regional Two North table,&nbsp; they will be in good spirits after their big home win, defeating Carlisle 20-0 on Saturday.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="800" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Callum-McClary-breaks-through-the-Windermere-defence-Ben-Challis.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334033" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Callum-McClary-breaks-through-the-Windermere-defence-Ben-Challis.jpg 800w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Callum-McClary-breaks-through-the-Windermere-defence-Ben-Challis-300x300.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Callum-McClary-breaks-through-the-Windermere-defence-Ben-Challis-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Callum-McClary-breaks-through-the-Windermere-defence-Ben-Challis-768x768.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Callum-McClary-breaks-through-the-Windermere-defence-Ben-Challis-146x146.jpg 146w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Callum McClary breaks through the Windermere defence (Ben Challis)</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The seconds had signed off for the seasonal break with a 26-5 win over Windermere.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Callum McClary, Lewis Pepper, Dan Craghill and Leo Horsbrugh scored the tries and there were&nbsp;three conversions by&nbsp; Ben Clark.</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
