    id: 334431,
    date: '2024-12-17T15:55:09',
    date_gmt: '2024-12-17T15:55:09',
    guid: { rendered: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/?p=334431' },
    modified: '2024-12-17T15:55:22',
    modified_gmt: '2024-12-17T15:55:22',
    slug: 'maryports-shiver-me-timbers-opens-this-week',
    status: 'publish',
    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/17/maryports-shiver-me-timbers-opens-this-week/',
    title: { rendered: 'Maryport&#8217;s Shiver Me Timbers opens this week' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="682" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-3.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334437" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-3.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-3-219x146.jpg 219w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Penny Watson</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>\u00a0A new pirate-themed adventure play area is about to open in Maryport.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The all-new Shiver Me Timbers,  on the town\u2019s harbourside, will open tomorrow, Wednesday December 18.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The existing wooden play equipment on the site had reached the end of its useful life and has been replaced.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A splash park will open on the site in spring.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Children from Our Lady\u2019s &amp; St Patrick\u2019s Primary School, Grasslot Primary School and Ewanrigg Junior School were the playpark\u2019s first official visitors.</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-4.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334438" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-4.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-4-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-4-220x146.jpg 220w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Penny Watson</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>he park\u2019s nautically-inspired design features slides, swings, a zipwire and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cumberland Council installed the equipment as part of \u00a312 million of Government-funded regeneration projects in the town. </p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="736" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-5.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334439" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-5.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-5-300x216.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-5-768x552.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-5-203x146.jpg 203w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Penny Watson</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>People were consulted on the design and more than 1,500 people responded. Seventy per cent of those who took part chose the pirate theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Maryport Town Council will manage the play area now the work is complete, with support from the team at the neighbouring Lake District Coast Aquarium.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Leader of Cumberland Council Mark Fryer said: \u201cThis is a fabulous new attraction on Maryport\u2019s historic harbourside and will appeal to children of all ages, and we have made sure there is some great accessible equipment too.</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="682" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-334441" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-1.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Shiver-Me-Timbers-Penny-Watson-1-219x146.jpg 219w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Picture: Penny Watson</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>\u201cWork is also well underway on the neighbouring outdoor event space, and the major improvements to the Maryport Activity Centre, which will also feature an indoor adventure play alongside a bigger and better Clip n\u2019 Climb attraction and a gym.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;They are all creating even more reasons to visit Maryport \u2013 with yet more destinations still to come.\u201d</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>\u00a0A new pirate-themed adventure play area is about to open in Maryport.</p>\n', protected: false },
