    type: 'post',
    link: 'https://cumbriacrack.com/2024/12/17/work-to-start-on-millom-all-weather-pitch-in-new-year/',
    title: { rendered: 'Work to start on Millom all-weather pitch in new year' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="307" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/208998-opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre.jpg" alt="opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre" class="wp-image-208999" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/208998-opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre.jpg 1024w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/208998-opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre-300x90.jpg 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/208998-opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre-768x230.jpg 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/208998-opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre-260x78.jpg 260w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/208998-opportunity-to-take-over-management-of-new-millom-leisure-centre-750x225.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Work on an all-weather pitch in Millom will start on Monday January 6 and will take around 12 weeks to complete.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>West Cumbrian contractor Thomas Armstrong has been appointed by Cumberland Council to undertake the refurbishment of the existing all-weather pitch, supporting the delivery of Millom Town Deal\u2019s Activating Community Health project.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new activity and leisure facility is one of four projects that make up the Millom Town Deal which secured \u00a320.6m from the Government\u2019s Town\u2019s Fund alongside a further \u00a38.7m in match funding.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>David Savage, chair of the Millom Town Deal Board, said: \u201cAs 2024 comes to a close, we can now look forward in 2025, the long awaited first spade in the ground, which is a significant milestone in transforming plans into real action.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cWe have listened to the community feedback and by working in collaboration with our delivery partners we have accelerated this work package so we can bring the 3G pitch back into operational use.\u201d</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The work on the leisure complex will proceed once the planning application has been approved. The Millom Town Deal Board and Cumberland Council remain committed to delivering the Town Deal projects for the benefit of the Millom and Haverigg communities.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Leader of Cumberland Council Mark Fryer added: \u201cThis will be an important step forward for the Millom Town Deal projects. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;It is great to see progress being made. Work continues on other parts of the Town Deal projects and momentum continues to build across this transformational programme.\u201d</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: '<p>Work on an all-weather pitch in Millom will start on Monday January 6 and will take around 12 weeks to complete.</p>\n', protected: false },
