    title: { rendered: 'Man jailed for three years for child sex offences' },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="768" height="563" src="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jordan-Emms.png" alt="" class="wp-image-334392" srcset="https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jordan-Emms.png 768w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jordan-Emms-300x220.png 300w, https://cumbriacrack.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Jordan-Emms-199x146.png 199w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Jordan Emms</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>A man from Barrow has been jailed for three years for child sex offences.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Jordan Emms, 38, appeared at Preston Crown Court today and sentenced for sexual assault by touching and causing/inciting a child to engage in sexual activity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A jury found Emms guilty of all charges against him after a six-day trial at Preston Crown Court last month.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The offences took place in Ulverston and relate to incidents involving one victim between 2018 and 2020.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Emms must also sign the sex offenders register.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Detective Sergeant Mike Wallace, of Cumbria police, said: \u201cEmms maintained that he had not committed these abhorrent offences, however a jury concluded that he was guilty.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cI hope the outcome of this trial, and sentence given to Emms today, can provide the victim with&nbsp;some reassurance that justice has been done.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cI would encourage anyone who has been a victim of sexual abuse&nbsp;to contact police so that our officers can investigate. Your report will be dealt with sensitively and professionally and you will be supported throughout our investigation.\u201d</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
